scanf("%d", &num);

int mod = num %2;

if (mod <0) {

    mod +=2;

}

list[i] = mod;

This way, list[i] is 0 or 1, just like in Python. So that's an important fix.

Otherwise, the code would fail for negative odd numbers. So the C code should include this adjustment. So putting it all together:

The code would read each number, compute mod 2, adjust for negative mod, then sum the array. Then proceed as before. So the corrected code:

